        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 3:39PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Arkinda, or 11 miles west of Horatio, moving east
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arkinda, Haworth, Shinewell, Cerrogordo, Goodwater, America, Moon,
Bokhoma, West Otis and West Line.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
